Drill

API DocumentationVersion 1.0MethodsDrill
Methods on drill

A drill is uniquely identified in the Drillster application by its code. The code is a short text string with no pre-defined length, and containing only upper and lower case letters, digits and the dash and underscore characters.

It is this code that is also used in the API to access individual drills.

Resources:

https://www.drillster.com/api/drill/[code].xml
https://www.drillster.com/api/drill/[code].json
GET drill

Description: retrieves meta data for a given drill code. This includes everything except the actual "known" and "unknown" entries. If the requested drill is in the requesting user's repertoire, the user's proficiency is included.

Note that the icon that is included in the response can have either a PNG or a JPEG format. It is therefore important to note the MIME type attribute in the attachment element.

Example XML request:

GET /api/drill/bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw.xml
Example XML response:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE drillster SYSTEM "http://www.drillster.com/api.dtd">

<response>
  <drill code="bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw" size="10">
    <name>Counting</name>
    <subject>French and German</subject>
    <description>Learn to count to ten in both French and German</description>
    <icon>
      <attachment mime="image/png">
        <![CDATA[]]>
      </attachment>
    </icon>
    <tags>
      <tag>counting</tag>
      <tag>french</tag>
      <tag>german</tag>
    </tags>
    <columns>
      <knownColumn name="English" arbiter="standard" />
      <unknownColumn name="French" arbiter="standard"/>
      <unknownColumn name="German" arbiter="german"/>
    </columns>
    <restrictions>
      <direction enforce="productive"/>
      <style side="known" enforce="multiplechoice"/>
      <style side="unknown" enforce="openended"/>
    </restrictions>
    <proficiency for="y0XcgsvsQrapE93VHQrvBQ">
      <receptive>5</receptive>
      <productive>17</productive>
      <overall>11</overall>
    </proficiency>
  </drill>
</response>
Example JSON request:

GET /api/drill/bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw.json
Example JSON response:

{"response": {"drill": {
  "code": "bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw",
  "columns": {
    "knownColumn": {
      "arbiter": "standard",
      "name": "English"
    },
    "unknownColumn": [
      {
        "arbiter": "standard",
        "name": "French"
      },
      {
        "arbiter": "german",
        "name": "German"
      }
    ]
  },
  "description": "Learn to count to ten in both French and German",
  "icon": {"attachment": {
    "content": "",
    "mime": "image/png"
  }},
  "name": "Counting",
  "proficiency": {
    "for": "y0XcgsvsQrapE93VHQrvBQ",
    "overall": "11",
    "productive": "17",
    "receptive": "5"
  },
  "restrictions": {
    "direction": {"enforce": "productive"},
    "style": [
      {
        "enforce": "multiplechoice",
        "side": "known"
      },
      {
        "enforce": "openended",
        "side": "unknown"
      }
    ]
  },
  "size": "10",
  "subject": "French and German",
  "tags": {"tag": [
    "counting",
    "french",
    "german"
  ]}
}}}
POST drill

This updates an existing drill. Meta data items are replaced where present in the request. Entries are appended to the drill, or replaced, as appropriate.

Example XML request:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE drillster SYSTEM "http://www.drillster.com/api.dtd">

<!-- POST /api/drill/bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw.xml -->

<request>
  <drill code="bDyD5Smt8CoMwIxVZHVHUw">
    <name>Counting</name>
    <subject>French and German</subject>
    <description>Learn to count to ten in both French and German</description>
    <tags>
      <tag>counting</tag>
      <tag>french</tag>
      <tag>german</tag>
    </tags>
    <columns>
      <knownColumn name="English" arbiter="standard" />
      <unknownColumn name="French" arbiter="standard"/>
      <unknownColumn name="German" arbiter="german"/>
    </columns>
    <restrictions>
      <direction enforce="productive"/>
      <style side="known" enforce="multiplechoice"/>
      <style side="unknown" enforce="openended"/>
    </restrictions>
    <entries>
      <entry>
        <known><term>one</term></known>
        <unknown name="French"><term>un</term><term>une</term></unknown>
        <unknown name="German"><term>eins</term><attachment mime="image/jpeg">...</attachment></unknown>
      </entry>
      <entry>
        <known><term>two</term></known>
        <unknown name="French"><term>deux</term></unknown>
        <unknown name="German"><term>zwei</term></unknown>
      </entry>
      <entry>
        <known><term>three</term></known>
        <unknown name="French"><term>trois</term></unknown>
        <unknown name="German"><term>drei</term></unknown>
      </entry>
    </entries>
  </drill>
</request>

  </drill>
</response>

PUT drill

This creates a new drill. The code for the new drill is returned as part of the response.

Example XML request:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE drillster SYSTEM "http://www.drillster.com/api.dtd">

<!-- PUT /api/drill.xml -->

<request>
  <drill>
    <name>Counting</name>
    <subject>French and German</subject>
    <description>Learn to count to ten in both French and German</description>
    <tags>
      <tag>counting</tag>
      <tag>french</tag>
      <tag>german</tag>
    </tags>
    <columns>
      <knownColumn name="English" arbiter="standard" />
      <unknownColumn name="French" arbiter="standard"/>
      <unknownColumn name="German" arbiter="german"/>
    </columns>
    <restrictions>
      <direction enforce="productive"/>
      <style side="known" enforce="multiplechoice"/>
      <style side="unknown" enforce="openended"/>
    </restrictions>
    <entries>
      <entry>
        <known><term>one</term></known>
        <unknown name="French"><term>un</term><term>une</term></unknown>
        <unknown name="German"><term>eins</term><attachment mime="image/jpeg">...</attachment></unknown>

      <entry>
        <known><term>two</term></known>

        <unknown name="French"><term>trois</term></unknown>

  </drill>
</request>
